## 5. PantheonOS Implementation (Pseudocode)

```python
class ArchetypeTensorEngine:
    def __init__(self, archetypes, tensor):
        self.A = archetypes      # dict of archetype vectors
        self.T = tensor          # n-d interaction tensor
    
    def rotate(self, name, theta):
        R = rotation_matrix(theta)
        self.A[name] = R @ self.A[name]

    def fuse(self, a, b, alpha=0.5, beta=0.5):
        # Fusion operator
        return alpha*self.A[a] + beta*self.A[b]

    def next_state(self, a, b):
        # Tensor contraction for next state computation
        return np.tensordot(self.T, np.outer(self.A[a], self.A[b]), axes=([0,1],[0,1]))
